WEBVTT

00:02.240 --> 00:04.368
OLIVER:
My name is Oliver Queen.

00:04.560 --> 00:07.803
For five years, I was stranded
on an island with only one goal:

00:09.600 --> 00:10.965
Survive.

00:11.120 --> 00:12.406
Oliver Queen is alive.

00:12.560 --> 00:14.847
OLIVER:
Now, I will fulfill my father's dying wish...

00:15.000 --> 00:17.241
...to use the list of names he left me...

00:17.400 --> 00:19.971
...and bring down those
who are poisoning my city.

00:21.600 --> 00:23.682
To do this,
I must become someone else.

00:24.720 --> 00:28.167
I must become something else.

00:28.320 --> 00:29.731
Previously on Arrow:

00:29.920 --> 00:32.082
You told me to stay away
from your family.

00:32.240 --> 00:36.211
But your family isn't staying away from me
which means something must be done.

00:36.360 --> 00:38.362
Where can I find the man
in this picture?

00:38.520 --> 00:41.126
Do you not think it convenient
you captured me easily?

00:41.280 --> 00:42.645
YAO FEI:
Run!

00:47.280 --> 00:49.044
[GRUNTS]

00:53.440 --> 00:55.920
FYERS: Do you even know
what this island really is?

00:56.080 --> 01:00.529
It's a prison.
What would you do in my position?

01:07.120 --> 01:10.124
[CLUB MUSIC PLAYING OVER RADIO]

01:14.280 --> 01:17.204
Whatever you're listening to,
it ain't music.

01:17.960 --> 01:19.200
[JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING OVER RADIO]

01:19.360 --> 01:23.001
- There ought to be a law.
- Well, there's not. So...

01:23.160 --> 01:25.766
[CLUB MUSIC PLAYING OVER RADIO]

01:26.320 --> 01:27.367
[GUN CLICKS]

01:33.160 --> 01:35.162
GUARD:
Yo, watch it.

01:42.440 --> 01:43.885
Hey, he's got a gun.

01:45.680 --> 01:47.762
[MEN GROANING]

01:50.360 --> 01:51.885
[BOTH COUGHING]

01:58.400 --> 01:59.606
[GUNFIRE]

02:19.720 --> 02:21.370
THEA:
Tahitian Green or Midnight Black?

02:21.520 --> 02:24.251
- What do you think?
- You've been dropping hints all week.

02:24.400 --> 02:26.289
Mom still isn't buying you a car.

02:26.440 --> 02:30.240
- I could not have said it better myself.
- Oliver got a car when he turned 18.

02:30.400 --> 02:33.722
Yeah, but I could back it out
of the driveway without hitting a tree.

02:33.920 --> 02:36.730
I do remember you taking the paint off
your dad's Maserati.

02:36.920 --> 02:39.161
- Hmm.
MOIRA: Thea, the party planner's waiting.

02:39.320 --> 02:41.084
Sorry to run off like this.

02:41.240 --> 02:43.208
But we have a convertible to go buy.

02:43.360 --> 02:45.681
OLIVER: Good luck.
MOIRA: Yes.

02:45.840 --> 02:49.606
- How's she holding up?
- Oh, she's okay.

02:49.760 --> 02:52.127
Thea thinks she's actually
a little bit too okay.

02:52.280 --> 02:54.044
- What do you mean?
- Just...

02:54.200 --> 02:57.647
...behaving erratically. Shut-in one minute,
running the company the next.

02:57.800 --> 03:00.963
Her husband is missing
and presumed who-knows-what.

03:01.120 --> 03:03.964
If anyone had an excuse to be erratic,
it's your mom.

03:04.160 --> 03:06.447
That's what I told Thea.

03:06.600 --> 03:11.322
Department's got the same comment about
this heist as the other two. No comment.

03:11.840 --> 03:14.047
S.C.P.D. may not be willing
to go on record...

03:14.200 --> 03:17.329
...but traffic cameras got the entire heist
in this exclusive.

03:17.480 --> 03:19.608
MAN: Shortly after 1 a.m.,
three masked robbers...

03:19.800 --> 03:23.088
...approached the armored vehicle
after launching what appears...

03:23.240 --> 03:25.811
TOMMY: That's why you keep
all your money offshore.

03:25.960 --> 03:28.247
MAN [ON TV]: One guard was
pronounced dead on the scene.

03:28.400 --> 03:30.641
The other died en route
to Starling General.

03:30.800 --> 03:33.007
Their identities have not yet
been released.

03:35.840 --> 03:38.684
DIGGLE: With all the guys up top,
you might want a side entrance...

03:38.840 --> 03:42.845
...for your, uh, Arrowcave.
OLIVER: Unh!

03:43.000 --> 03:47.767
Just put one in. South alleyway.
Ah. There's something I wanna show you.

03:48.360 --> 03:51.364
You're into online dating
and you need help with your profile.

03:51.520 --> 03:54.967
Not exactly.
But there's somebody I'd like to meet.

03:55.760 --> 03:59.207
Yeah, I read about this.
Third truck to get hit this month.

03:59.360 --> 04:01.408
I saw it on the news this morning.

04:01.560 --> 04:04.245
Couldn't figure out
why it seemed so familiar.

04:04.400 --> 04:07.131
Then I remembered this. Kandahar, '09.

04:07.280 --> 04:09.726
The Marines took out
a Taliban transport vehicle.

04:09.880 --> 04:11.644
DIGGLE:
Yeah. Well, there's a reason...

04:11.800 --> 04:15.850
...why that looks similar. These guys run
the same technique. Where'd you find this?

04:16.000 --> 04:19.322
Researching someone.
Bodyguard who works for a security firm.

04:19.480 --> 04:23.690
Blackhawk Squad Protection Group.
His name is Ted Gaynor.

04:23.840 --> 04:27.640
Oliver, Ted Gaynor was my commanding
officer my first tour in Afghanistan.

04:31.200 --> 04:34.602
Dig, I'm sorry...

04:37.360 --> 04:39.761
...but Gaynor's on the list.

04:39.960 --> 04:42.201
Gaynor's a few
hundred thousand dollars short.

04:42.360 --> 04:44.761
I never said it was just
1 percenters, did I?

04:44.920 --> 04:49.528
This guy saved my life.
Received a commendation for it.

04:49.720 --> 04:52.371
Don't care what your book says,
he's not a stick-up man.

04:52.560 --> 04:55.609
- You haven't known him a long time.
- We both kept in contact...

04:55.760 --> 04:57.000
...since we got stateside.

04:57.160 --> 04:59.925
Six months ago,
he even offered me a job at Blackhawk.

05:00.080 --> 05:02.208
Trust me, you don't know this man
like I do.

05:02.400 --> 05:06.564
I know in Afghanistan his training specialty
was M32 multiple grenade launchers.

05:06.720 --> 05:08.802
The exact same weapon used
in these heists.

05:08.960 --> 05:12.203
Not exactly something you find
at your local sporting goods store.

05:12.360 --> 05:15.523
Two months ago we found out
this wasn't even your father's book.

05:15.680 --> 05:19.321
Written by whoever hired the other archer.
Doesn't that beg the question...

05:19.480 --> 05:23.929
-...what else you could be wrong about?
- I can be wrong. The list isn't.

05:24.080 --> 05:28.085
Now, I'm gonna have a pointed
conversation with Mr. Gaynor tonight.

05:28.240 --> 05:29.810
We'll see what he has to say.

05:31.920 --> 05:34.924
I understand
if you wanna take the week off.

05:35.080 --> 05:36.844
Yeah, well, thank you.

05:38.520 --> 05:39.681
Sir.

06:09.840 --> 06:10.921
[MEN CHATTERING]

06:37.800 --> 06:39.802
[SOLIDER SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

06:41.320 --> 06:44.244
SOLDIER:
Different day, same slop.

06:44.840 --> 06:46.922
- You new?
OLIVER: Yeah.

06:47.080 --> 06:48.127
[SOLDIER CHUCKLES]

06:48.280 --> 06:51.682
SOLDIER: Don't worry. Took me a year
to find my way around the island.

06:52.280 --> 06:53.566
OLIVER:
Well, hey, hey, hey.

06:55.880 --> 06:59.009
I'm supposed to be transporting
a prisoner.

06:59.160 --> 07:01.242
Chinese guy who wears a green hood?

07:01.440 --> 07:03.761
SOLDIER: Sounds like the guy
they took to east camp.

07:03.920 --> 07:06.241
I'm heading over that way.
You can hitch a ride.

07:07.040 --> 07:08.883
Let's go, come on.

07:19.040 --> 07:23.125
Hold up, hold up. Unit one, two.

07:26.880 --> 07:28.564
[FYE RS GROAN I NG]

07:38.360 --> 07:41.409
That wall over there
still has to be taped and textured.

07:41.600 --> 07:45.571
I need you to grout the hallway floor as
soon as they're done with the tile install.

07:45.720 --> 07:47.404
[PHONE BEEPING]

07:47.560 --> 07:48.641
MAN:
All right.

07:49.920 --> 07:51.888
- Yeah.
- Hey, Tommy.

07:52.040 --> 07:55.044
- Dad, I am really busy.
- Tommy, I know things have been...

07:55.240 --> 07:57.129
...well, strained between us since--

07:57.280 --> 07:59.760
Since you cut me off
and told me that I was a loser?

07:59.920 --> 08:02.571
I was just trying
to jolt you into adulthood.

08:02.720 --> 08:05.485
And look at you now.
You've got your first job, heh.

08:05.640 --> 08:07.847
My tough love worked.

08:08.000 --> 08:09.490
What do you want, Dad?

08:10.440 --> 08:13.603
Nothing more than to share a meal
with my son.

08:13.800 --> 08:14.926
Dinner, tomorrow night?

08:15.080 --> 08:17.287
- Laurel and I have plans.
MALCOLM: Bring her along.

08:17.440 --> 08:21.365
I think it's time I got to know her
a little better. Tommy...

08:22.800 --> 08:26.282
...I've said some pretty hurtful things
and I regret them.

08:27.280 --> 08:28.691
But you're still my son...

08:28.840 --> 08:31.969
...and I still want
what I've always wanted.

08:33.880 --> 08:35.769
For us to be close.

08:37.840 --> 08:40.605
Let me check with Laurel
and I'll get back to you.

08:52.400 --> 08:53.970
[DART GUN FIRING]

09:14.240 --> 09:15.765
[GRUNTS]

09:16.400 --> 09:18.289
Ted, we're gonna have a conversation.

09:18.440 --> 09:22.968
You make a move, go for a gun,
anything and things will end badly for you.

09:23.160 --> 09:24.161
[GUN COCKS]

09:24.320 --> 09:26.368
Put the bow down.

09:45.040 --> 09:46.769
[SIGHS]

09:56.680 --> 09:57.681
[SIGHS]

09:57.840 --> 10:00.047
It's all clear. You okay?

10:00.240 --> 10:03.005
Uh,yeah.

10:03.840 --> 10:08.402
Well, I gotta talk to my boss
but after what I just saw...

10:08.560 --> 10:11.006
...I'd say you're as good as hired.

10:11.160 --> 10:13.401
Hell of a job interview, Ted.

10:13.560 --> 10:16.291
Usually the vigilante
only goes after rich schmucks.

10:16.440 --> 10:19.330
Any reason why he would change
his MO for you?

10:21.040 --> 10:22.087
[SIGHS]

10:22.240 --> 10:27.121
You've known me a long time, John.
What do you think?

10:29.720 --> 10:31.051
[SIGHS]

10:31.200 --> 10:33.407
I think he made a mistake.

10:34.320 --> 10:36.322
Got the wrong guy.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.642
OLIVER:
I could've shot you, killed you.

10:42.800 --> 10:45.201
- What the hell?
- Not gonna let you William Tell...

10:45.360 --> 10:47.522
-...an innocent man.
- Gaynor isn't innocent.

10:47.680 --> 10:49.842
You seem to think that
because of your book...

10:50.040 --> 10:53.726
-...which you trust more than you trust me.
- I trust my father.

10:53.920 --> 10:58.209
And he explained to me that every name
on that list has a reason to be there.

10:58.360 --> 11:02.365
You took that book off your father's
dead body. How could he be so chatty?

11:04.160 --> 11:08.085
A few years ago, I found a message
he left me explaining the list.

11:08.240 --> 11:10.925
How was that possible?
You were on a deserted island.

11:11.080 --> 11:14.004
I didn't say that I found it on the island.

11:15.480 --> 11:18.768
Diggle, for the past four months,
I've lied to...

11:18.920 --> 11:22.561
...hurt and hid things
from all the people that I care about.

11:22.720 --> 11:27.601
Do you really think that I would do all this
if I wasn't sure?

11:33.520 --> 11:36.126
Oliver, listen,
Gaynor got me into Blackhawk.

11:36.280 --> 11:38.282
And I'm gonna prove he's innocent.

11:39.960 --> 11:41.007
And if he's isn't?

11:41.160 --> 11:42.207
[GUN COCKS]

11:44.200 --> 11:46.168
You owe me that.

11:48.000 --> 11:49.286
You owe me at least that.

11:57.280 --> 12:00.409
- Were you stationed by the perimeter?
OLIVER: Yes.

12:00.560 --> 12:04.565
- And your report?
OLIVER: Everything's good, sir. No trouble.

12:04.720 --> 12:08.566
- How long have you been stationed here?
OLIVER: Uh, just arrived, sir.

12:09.280 --> 12:11.123
Yes, you do seem rather green.

12:13.680 --> 12:18.607
I don't recall the submarine bringing
in a phalanx of new troops lately.

12:21.040 --> 12:22.849
OLIVER:
Submarine?

12:23.000 --> 12:25.810
I thought everybody came in
to the island on the plane.

12:27.920 --> 12:30.082
Indeed they do.

12:35.560 --> 12:38.040
I think you've tried on
every dress in the city.

12:38.200 --> 12:39.247
Heh. Totally worth it.

12:39.440 --> 12:40.487
[CHUCKLES]

12:40.640 --> 12:41.766
My friends are gonna freak.

12:41.920 --> 12:44.651
Yes, well, if your father were still alive,
he'd freak too.

12:44.800 --> 12:46.882
Though in an entirely different way.

12:47.040 --> 12:50.249
Heh, like when he saw what I was
wearing to my first boy-girl dance?

12:50.400 --> 12:54.962
That poor boy you went with.
Oh, Robert scared him to death.

12:55.120 --> 12:59.762
You know, Dad used to say his saddest
day would be when I turned 18.

13:01.280 --> 13:04.443
Now he's gone
and I'm the one that's sad.

13:07.160 --> 13:08.844
[PHONE RINGS]

13:09.000 --> 13:10.764
Ah, sorry.

13:13.000 --> 13:14.411
I need to take this.

13:16.440 --> 13:18.044
Hello?

13:19.080 --> 13:22.209
Yes, I understand
but I'm with my daughter.

13:25.080 --> 13:27.606
All right. I'll be there.

13:30.000 --> 13:31.081
[SIGHS]

13:31.240 --> 13:32.651
We were gonna
spend the whole day together.

13:32.800 --> 13:36.282
I know, but, uh...

13:36.440 --> 13:39.728
...compliance needs to file
the 8K connected...

13:39.920 --> 13:43.845
...to my assuming Walter's position
at the company and they can't wait.

13:45.600 --> 13:47.250
I'm sorry.

13:49.400 --> 13:54.042
- Is everything okay? You look worried.
- Not worried. Just...

13:57.120 --> 13:59.043
My father called.

13:59.760 --> 14:01.250
Oh.

14:02.240 --> 14:04.686
- And how did that go?
- He invited us to dinner.

14:04.840 --> 14:06.046
For tonight.

14:06.240 --> 14:07.287
Oh.

14:07.440 --> 14:09.841
Yeah. Apparently,
he wants to mend some fences.

14:10.000 --> 14:12.685
But thanks to him, I can't afford a fence.

14:12.840 --> 14:14.922
I assume he's got some other agenda.

14:15.120 --> 14:17.043
Well, there's only one way to find out.

14:17.200 --> 14:20.761
And maybe he really is trying to extend
an olive branch.

14:23.160 --> 14:26.209
You really do look for the best in people,
don't you?

14:26.680 --> 14:28.364
Lucky for you.

14:28.520 --> 14:30.090
[CHUCKLES]

14:36.080 --> 14:38.606
I'm sorry to have to pull you away
from your family.

14:38.760 --> 14:40.000
What do you want, Malcolm?

14:40.160 --> 14:42.527
We have a problem with your friend,
Carl Ballard.

14:43.440 --> 14:45.169
He's trying to gentrify the Glades.

14:47.320 --> 14:49.163
Carl knows that's not part of the plan.

14:49.360 --> 14:53.570
Which is why you're gonna shut him down.
You're his friend. He'll listen to you.

14:55.840 --> 14:59.811
You want me to help you with Carl,
I want something in return.

15:00.320 --> 15:03.051
Proof Walter's still alive.

15:05.200 --> 15:06.440
My word isn't enough?

15:06.600 --> 15:07.681
[MOIRA SCOFFS]

15:07.880 --> 15:11.965
What's that saying? "Trust, but verify"?

15:15.160 --> 15:17.447
Words to live by.

15:28.080 --> 15:30.970
GAYNOR: Two days later,
I'm still digging regurgitated tacos...

15:31.120 --> 15:34.681
...out of the car vents and he asks me
why I won't turn on the AC?

15:34.840 --> 15:35.887
[LAUGHING]

15:36.080 --> 15:38.731
All right, you win.
Bodyguarding Queen was never that bad.

15:38.880 --> 15:43.090
Six years serving, the only thing I'm
qualified for is babysitting spoiled brats.

15:43.240 --> 15:45.004
Ted, they're not all like that.

15:45.160 --> 15:48.004
I haven't met one yet
that would survive a single day in-country.

15:48.160 --> 15:49.207
Hmm.

15:49.360 --> 15:51.283
Makes me wonder
what I was doing over there.

15:51.440 --> 15:52.601
CARLY:
Specialty of the house.

15:53.400 --> 15:55.323
- Thank you, Carly.
- Uh-uh, where is my cake?

15:55.480 --> 15:59.121
Tired of listening to you complain
about the cleaners shrinking your suits.

15:59.280 --> 16:00.964
- Oh, yeah.
- Heh.

16:01.760 --> 16:02.807
[SCOFFS]

16:05.640 --> 16:08.644
- She likes you.
- She's my sister-in-law, Ted.

16:08.800 --> 16:13.044
Not anymore. Your brother's gone, John.

16:13.240 --> 16:15.641
But you are here.

16:18.440 --> 16:19.851
Car's waiting outside.

16:20.040 --> 16:22.691
We got a client to drop off
at the art gallery opening.

16:22.840 --> 16:24.251
GAYNOR:
You remember Paul Knox?

16:24.400 --> 16:27.404
He was a couple of ranks under us
back in the 'Stan.

16:29.880 --> 16:31.962
Good to be working with you.

16:35.680 --> 16:37.523
I'll be outside.

16:41.160 --> 16:42.924
Didn't know Knox
worked at Blackhawk.

16:43.080 --> 16:45.924
They recruited him
when his tour ended last month.

16:46.080 --> 16:47.241
Mm-hm.

16:47.440 --> 16:49.966
People change, John.

16:50.120 --> 16:52.327
And everyone deserves
a chance to prove it.

17:04.000 --> 17:05.286
[TYPING ON KEYBOARD]

17:05.440 --> 17:07.044
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

17:09.359 --> 17:10.406
[DOOR OPENING]

17:10.560 --> 17:13.803
OLIVER: Knocking is not just a suggestion.
- I need to talk to you.

17:13.960 --> 17:17.406
Thea, I'm not telling you
if Mom's getting you a car.

17:17.560 --> 17:20.803
Heh, it's not about that.

17:20.960 --> 17:24.885
Remember last week when I asked you
if you thought Mom was acting weird?

17:25.040 --> 17:28.601
- Yep.
- Well, I found out why.

17:28.760 --> 17:30.967
She's hooking up with Tommy's dad.

17:31.120 --> 17:32.360
[SCOFFS]

17:32.520 --> 17:36.127
- That's insane.
- I just saw them together.

17:36.320 --> 17:39.767
-It's happening all over again.
- What are you talking about?

17:41.600 --> 17:42.647
Um...

17:45.200 --> 17:50.570
A couple months
before you and Dad left on the Gambit...

17:50.720 --> 17:53.644
-...Mom and Dad were arguing a lot.
- About what?

17:53.840 --> 18:00.371
I don't know. But she was having a lot
of these lunch meetings with Mr. Merlyn.

18:00.520 --> 18:01.885
And now Walter's gone too...

18:02.040 --> 18:05.931
...and Mom and Mr. Merlyn
are back at it. It's gross.

18:06.800 --> 18:11.681
Mom never would've cheated on Dad.
She's not cheating on Walter.

18:11.840 --> 18:12.887
[SIGHS]

18:13.960 --> 18:19.126
You don't wanna believe because you have
this perfect image of Mom in your head.

18:19.320 --> 18:26.283
That's not who she is, Ollie.
She's a liar and a cheater.

18:27.240 --> 18:30.369
And you really don't know her at all.

18:44.960 --> 18:46.849
Malcolm and I, having an affair?

18:47.000 --> 18:49.082
That it started when Dad was still alive.

18:49.240 --> 18:52.244
- Why would she think that?
- She says you and Dad were fighting.

18:52.440 --> 18:55.125
- Oh, dear God.
- Mom?

18:55.320 --> 18:59.325
-It's not your concern, sweetheart.
- Thea made it my concern.

19:02.920 --> 19:05.127
What was going on?

19:11.360 --> 19:17.641
Robert was unfaithful to me.
Repeatedly.

19:19.320 --> 19:23.245
It made our marriage difficult,
to say the least.

19:24.280 --> 19:27.762
I'm sorry. But your father wasn't always
the man you thought he was.

19:27.920 --> 19:28.967
[SCOFFS]

19:29.120 --> 19:30.645
I know you thought he walked on water.

19:30.800 --> 19:33.565
But you see, that's how I wanted you
to remember him...

19:33.720 --> 19:35.688
...as a good man who loved you.

19:35.840 --> 19:41.370
That's how I want Thea to remember him.
So promise me you'll keep it a secret.

19:43.360 --> 19:44.930
Of course.

19:48.600 --> 19:51.046
_Mom?
'Yes?

19:51.200 --> 19:54.647
Why would Thea think you and Mr. Meryln
are still sneaking around?

19:55.800 --> 19:58.485
Well, I can't imagine.

20:00.480 --> 20:02.050
Have you seen him lately?

20:03.480 --> 20:05.209
Oliver.

20:05.360 --> 20:06.646
[CHUCKLES]

20:06.800 --> 20:10.088
He's been the CEO
of Merlyn Global Group for years.

20:10.240 --> 20:13.801
I've been running
Queen Consolidated mere weeks.

20:13.960 --> 20:17.282
Yes, I occasionally go
and ask for advice.

20:21.000 --> 20:22.809
Is my interrogation over?

20:42.240 --> 20:43.890
FYERS:
See, this is where we, uh...

20:44.520 --> 20:49.686
...detain prisoners prone to running off
before I've finished with them.

20:49.840 --> 20:50.887
[OLIVER GRUNTS]

20:51.840 --> 20:53.001
[THUDS]

20:54.400 --> 20:55.526
[OLIVER COUGHS]

20:59.840 --> 21:01.171
[PANTS]

21:01.360 --> 21:04.330
Prisoners like you, Mr. Queen.

21:09.920 --> 21:14.130
At Christmas one year,
Tommy wanted a puppy.

21:14.760 --> 21:17.730
He wanted to name it Arthur,
as in King Arthur...

21:18.440 --> 21:20.010
...because he's a Merlyn.

21:20.160 --> 21:23.050
Heh. Well, you used to be
so incredibly adorable.

21:23.200 --> 21:24.725
- I still am.
- Heh.

21:24.880 --> 21:26.245
My wife would've liked you, Laurel.

21:28.520 --> 21:29.931
LAUREL:
I wish I would've known her.

21:30.080 --> 21:32.447
She passed away
before Tommy and I became friends.

21:32.640 --> 21:36.326
She was killed.
There's no need to be polite about it.

21:36.520 --> 21:38.443
You are just a ray of sunshine today.

21:38.600 --> 21:41.490
Please forgive me.
Talking about my wife has a tendency...

21:41.640 --> 21:44.007
...to make me a little bit maudlin.

21:51.320 --> 21:53.846
And here I was beginning
to think my days of being...

21:54.040 --> 21:55.883
...Oliver's geek were coming to an end.

21:56.080 --> 22:00.642
- Is that your way of saying you missed me?
- No, but if that works for you, go with it.

22:00.800 --> 22:03.201
Heh. A friend is running
a scavenger hunt...

22:03.360 --> 22:06.443
...and there's a case
of Lafite Rothschild 1982...

22:06.600 --> 22:08.728
-...waiting at the end.
- Oh, I love red wine.

22:08.880 --> 22:12.362
But in order to find it,
I first need to get through this.

22:13.600 --> 22:14.681
Hmm.

22:14.840 --> 22:16.205
Security fob.

22:23.320 --> 22:24.367
[DEVICE BEEPS]

22:25.200 --> 22:26.486
[TYPING ON KEYBOARD]

22:26.640 --> 22:28.324
It's PIN protected.

22:28.480 --> 22:32.166
Response goes back to a company called
Blackhawk Squad Protection Group.

22:32.320 --> 22:34.561
My friend had his bodyguard
set it up for him.

22:34.720 --> 22:37.326
Personally, I think it's cheating,
but whatever.

22:37.480 --> 22:41.166
This is a military-grade cryptographic
security protocol.

22:41.320 --> 22:45.689
- Your friend really went to all this trouble?
- The idle rich are hard to entertain.

22:46.760 --> 22:52.642
Listen, you get through it
and one of those bottles of wine is yours.

23:04.680 --> 23:07.650
This has been lovely, Mr. Merlyn.
Thank you.

23:07.800 --> 23:09.086
Thank you for joining me.

23:09.280 --> 23:11.965
It's been wonderful
getting to know you better.

23:12.600 --> 23:15.410
If Tommy doesn't mind me
mixing business with pleasure...

23:15.560 --> 23:18.040
...I could use your signature on these.

23:31.000 --> 23:32.889
You wanna shut down
Mom's free clinic?

23:33.040 --> 23:36.681
-It's not hers anymore, Tommy.
- That clinic meant everything to Mom.

23:36.840 --> 23:41.164
You were 8. I don't think you were in
a position to know what was important.

23:41.320 --> 23:43.561
- I just need your signature--
TOMMY: Stop.

23:44.080 --> 23:47.562
This dinner was never about
getting to know Laurel...

23:47.720 --> 23:49.006
...it was about this.

24:00.800 --> 24:03.041
You haven't changed
and you never will.

24:04.520 --> 24:08.730
It's about time that I learn that
and stop letting you disappoint me.

24:10.200 --> 24:12.089
We're leaving.

24:15.400 --> 24:18.927
- This clinic was his mother's.
MALCOLM: Yes.

24:19.080 --> 24:20.923
And his mother taught him a lesson...

24:21.080 --> 24:24.163
...that the world is a harsh
and unforgiving place.

24:24.320 --> 24:25.765
When did she teach him that?

24:29.720 --> 24:33.611
When she was lying dead in the street
with a bullet in her head.

24:36.320 --> 24:38.209
Good night.

24:42.640 --> 24:45.610
GAYNOR: Management keeps things
running smooth, which is nice.

24:45.760 --> 24:48.081
Better than going to war
with the army you got, right?

24:48.240 --> 24:51.642
Heh. Indeed. Indeed.

24:52.160 --> 24:55.209
So, Ted, are you the reason
Knox is working for Blackhawk?

24:55.360 --> 24:58.284
Look, I know you don't like the guy.

24:58.440 --> 25:00.966
I wasn't his biggest fan either.

25:01.120 --> 25:04.169
But jobs are hard to come by
for everybody these days.

25:04.320 --> 25:06.004
And guys like us?

25:06.160 --> 25:09.369
When all anyone thinks you're qualified for
is shooting at people?

25:09.520 --> 25:11.170
If I hadn't gotten Knox this job...

25:11.720 --> 25:16.408
...chances are he'd be out knocking over
liquor stores or robbing banks.

25:20.440 --> 25:21.487
[PHONE RINGING]

25:23.320 --> 25:25.402
- What'd you get?
FELICITY: Your friend's bodyguard...

25:25.560 --> 25:27.130
-...gave him the wrong fob.
- Why?

25:27.280 --> 25:30.124
Well, once I got past Blackhawk's
authentication system...

25:30.280 --> 25:33.329
...there wasn't anything
about a scavenger hunt.

25:33.480 --> 25:35.721
Just a directory and...

25:35.880 --> 25:39.043
Well, I think you've stumbled onto
or gotten me to stumble onto...

25:39.200 --> 25:41.567
-...something pretty illegal.
- Define illegal.

25:41.720 --> 25:46.203
Oh, you know, robbing an armored car
with grenade launchers and tear gas.

25:46.360 --> 25:48.169
- What?
- Someone at Blackhawk...

25:48.320 --> 25:50.607
...was using their system
to store schedules...

25:50.760 --> 25:53.286
...for the city's
seven major armored car carriers.

25:53.440 --> 25:58.048
Including the three that have been hit. We
should provide this information to police.

25:58.240 --> 26:00.402
They should be able
to predict the next heist.

26:00.560 --> 26:01.846
Hold on, Felicity.

26:02.000 --> 26:04.765
I don't wanna get you in trouble.
Do me a favor.

26:04.920 --> 26:08.686
Forward that directory on to me
and I'll get it to the police personally.

26:08.840 --> 26:10.649
Thank you.

26:12.600 --> 26:14.523
So no wine then?

26:40.200 --> 26:41.201
[MAN GRUNTS]

26:41.920 --> 26:43.365
[GUNFIRE]

27:01.720 --> 27:02.926
[GROANING]

27:03.080 --> 27:05.287
Blake? Blake? Come on, man, come on.

27:05.440 --> 27:06.726
[GRUNTS]

27:11.880 --> 27:12.927
[GRUNTS]

27:13.720 --> 27:18.282
- Blake is hit. He's hit!
- Come on, come on!

27:18.440 --> 27:20.249
Go. Drive, drive, drive.

27:20.400 --> 27:21.731
[TIRES SCREECH]

27:34.280 --> 27:35.930
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

27:37.840 --> 27:39.808
[CROWD CHEERING]

27:44.280 --> 27:46.089
Oh, God, check it out. Check it out.

27:46.240 --> 27:49.528
- Convertible. Oh, my God.
- You must be so surprised.

27:49.680 --> 27:54.288
Isn't everything absolutely perfect?
Except for if Dad were here.

27:55.080 --> 27:58.801
If Dad were here,
he'd say you look beautiful.

28:00.960 --> 28:02.928
- Oh, excuse me a sec.
OLIVER: Mm-hm.

28:09.520 --> 28:12.410
DIGGLE: I heard the Hood foiled
an armored car heist earlier.

28:12.560 --> 28:14.244
Gaynor wasn't running
the rocket launcher.

28:14.400 --> 28:16.243
I was with him the whole time.

28:17.240 --> 28:19.004
Looks like you were right.

28:19.160 --> 28:22.528
If someone at Blackhawk is involved,
I'd put my money on Knox.

28:22.720 --> 28:25.724
He started right before the heists began.
He has training.

28:25.880 --> 28:27.291
Okay, I injured one of them.

28:27.440 --> 28:30.205
He was bleeding badly
when they made off in their van.

28:30.360 --> 28:33.170
If any of Knox's blood is in one
of the motor pool vans...

28:33.320 --> 28:35.049
-...we'll know.
- I'm going with you.

28:35.200 --> 28:38.966
No, listen, you have this party
and I told you I would handle this.

28:39.120 --> 28:42.647
- Any problems, you're a phone call away.
- Hey.

28:43.760 --> 28:45.410
Head on a swivel.

28:46.160 --> 28:48.481
That's the way I was born, man.

28:53.680 --> 28:56.126
- Happy birthday.
- Oh, thank you.

28:56.280 --> 28:59.250
We have a special birthday gift for you.
It's called Vertigo.

28:59.400 --> 29:01.482
Supposed to make you feel all floaty.

29:01.640 --> 29:05.167
Ah, heh, if my morn caught me with this,
I wouldn't make it to 19.

29:05.320 --> 29:08.210
I'm gonna go put it upstairs
and then I'll be right back down.

29:18.120 --> 29:20.600
Moira, I have a little something for you.

29:21.520 --> 29:22.851
MOIRA:
Walter.

29:24.360 --> 29:28.251
I did as you asked.
Now it's your turn to do as I asked.

29:28.400 --> 29:32.644
MOIRA: I'll take care of it.
- Thank you, Moira.

29:37.480 --> 29:42.247
- At my party. Right here in front of me?
- No, Thea, you don't understand.

29:42.400 --> 29:46.564
Walter hasn't been gone two months
and you're already cheating on him.

29:46.760 --> 29:49.331
- Just like you cheated on Dad--
- No, I never cheated--

29:49.480 --> 29:53.405
- Like I would believe anything you say.
- Thea. Thea.

29:53.600 --> 29:58.128
I wish it had been you
that was on that boat.

30:56.480 --> 30:58.084
[GUNS COCK]

30:58.240 --> 31:00.561
KNOX:
I had a feeling you'd show up.

31:01.640 --> 31:03.404
DIGGLE:
Yeah? Why is that, Knox?

31:03.560 --> 31:06.450
KNOX: Right after Gaynor got you hired,
someone hacked our system.

31:06.600 --> 31:08.523
First person to ever make it through.

31:08.720 --> 31:12.725
- You wanna tell me how you did it?
- Not really sure.

31:12.880 --> 31:15.281
- He didn't think you'd be very cooperative.
- Who?

31:21.760 --> 31:22.841
Hey, John.

31:29.600 --> 31:33.366
- Ted, you're part of this?
GAYNOR: No, not part of.

31:33.840 --> 31:37.208
My men. My mission.

31:37.360 --> 31:39.249
Mission?

31:39.400 --> 31:43.564
- This isn't Afghanistan.
- Oh, don't I know that.

31:43.720 --> 31:48.647
Over there, we were trusted with millions
of dollars in weapons and personnel.

31:48.840 --> 31:51.207
We were conquerors.

31:51.360 --> 31:54.284
And now? We're nannies with Tasers.

31:54.440 --> 31:55.487
[SCOFFS]

31:57.080 --> 32:00.687
So that gives you the right to steal?

32:00.840 --> 32:05.004
- To kill innocent civilians?
- I'm not gonna convince you I'm right.

32:05.160 --> 32:09.006
- I am gonna convince you to join the team.
- Heh. Yeah, now I know you're crazy.

32:09.840 --> 32:12.969
Tonight was supposed to be our last score.
Because of the Hood...

32:13.120 --> 32:15.009
...we struck out.

32:15.200 --> 32:20.809
Now we're down a man. Good thing
you're qualified to take his place.

32:21.000 --> 32:22.047
[SCOFFS]

32:22.200 --> 32:25.363
I think your convincing
is gonna have to be a lot more convincing.

32:27.720 --> 32:30.929
Copy that. Cavanaugh.

32:31.080 --> 32:32.127
[DOOR OPENS]

32:33.160 --> 32:34.207
[CARLY GRUNTING]

32:34.360 --> 32:36.567
DIGGLE:
Carly.

32:36.760 --> 32:38.125
You son of a bitch.

32:39.160 --> 32:43.563
- No, don't. Don't. Wait. Don't.
- Knox.

32:44.120 --> 32:45.167
[MUFFLED SCREAMS]

32:48.560 --> 32:51.484
You both can die tonight, John.

32:51.640 --> 32:55.804
Or once we do this, we're on a plane
and she can go home to your nephew.

32:55.960 --> 32:57.928
[OVER COMM]
It's your call.

33:26.640 --> 33:27.687
[HORN HONKS]

33:33.680 --> 33:34.727
Oh.

33:36.120 --> 33:38.202
Come on, let's go. Ugh.

33:38.360 --> 33:40.647
KNOX:
Oh, you shouldn't have done that, Dig.

33:40.800 --> 33:42.882
Now you gotta watch us
kill your girlfriend.

33:43.080 --> 33:46.243
- No, please don't.
DIGGLE: You're forgetting one thing, guys.

33:46.400 --> 33:47.970
Oh, yeah? What's that?

33:48.120 --> 33:50.646
I'm the one with the grenade launcher.

33:52.520 --> 33:54.284
Carly, get out of there.

33:54.440 --> 33:55.441
[GRUNTS]

34:04.280 --> 34:05.327
[PANTS]

34:35.600 --> 34:37.648
DIGGLE: Freeze!
- Oh.

34:40.080 --> 34:41.127
[GASPS]

34:41.280 --> 34:42.884
DIGGLE:
Drop it, Ted.

34:43.040 --> 34:44.565
Or I swear...

34:44.719 --> 34:47.929
Don't posture.

34:49.239 --> 34:51.607
You're not gonna do it.

34:52.639 --> 34:55.962
You can't. I can see it in your eyes.

35:13.920 --> 35:17.641
- You're late.
- You knew I was coming?

35:21.440 --> 35:25.286
DIGGLE: Next time you plant a bug
on someone, be more subtle about it.

35:26.640 --> 35:30.247
- I wish you'd trusted me though.
- I trusted you.

35:31.600 --> 35:35.446
But them, never.

35:37.040 --> 35:38.041
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

35:39.680 --> 35:41.762
You should get out of here.

35:46.800 --> 35:48.689
John.

35:56.480 --> 35:58.847
Carly, are you okay?

35:59.640 --> 36:02.211
OFFICER: Turn around
and put your hands where I can see them.

36:04.240 --> 36:05.924
[CLUB MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

36:13.880 --> 36:14.927
[TIRES SCREECH]

36:16.720 --> 36:17.767
[GLASS SHATTERS]

36:33.040 --> 36:36.044
[WOMAN SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY OVER PA]

36:41.120 --> 36:43.043
Oh, Thea.

36:43.200 --> 36:46.363
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

36:46.520 --> 36:48.682
Just headachey, really.

36:49.480 --> 36:53.485
- The car, is it...?
- The car isn't important right now.

36:53.640 --> 36:55.369
[SIGHS]

36:55.560 --> 36:57.244
Do you remember what happened,
sweetheart?

36:57.440 --> 36:58.487
[SCOFFS]

36:59.520 --> 37:01.887
Just go away.

37:03.280 --> 37:08.366
- Thea, please.
- I said, I'm fine.

37:17.640 --> 37:18.687
[PHONE RINGING]

37:19.240 --> 37:20.844
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
ON TELEVISION]

37:22.440 --> 37:24.602
Your father's even beginning
to call me now.

37:24.800 --> 37:26.768
Don't waste your minutes.

37:27.360 --> 37:28.407
[SIGHS]

37:29.440 --> 37:33.081
Your father's a jerk,
but he's still your father.

37:39.520 --> 37:42.922
I think, in his own way...

37:43.080 --> 37:46.289
I think he sees himself
as protecting you somehow.

37:46.440 --> 37:49.364
Yeah, he is really good
at using my dead mother...

37:49.520 --> 37:51.522
...for an excuse for being a jerk.

37:52.440 --> 37:54.204
You never talk about your mother.

37:56.320 --> 38:00.006
I was only 8. I don't remember much
about what happened.

38:01.840 --> 38:03.808
But after?

38:04.360 --> 38:08.001
My father completely shut me out.

38:14.200 --> 38:16.168
And then he went away.

38:17.880 --> 38:22.363
He was gone for a year, maybe two.

38:22.520 --> 38:29.210
I was 8 and he left me.
That is who my father is.

38:31.040 --> 38:33.611
He only cares about himself.

38:51.320 --> 38:53.209
- Cops give you a hard time?
DIGGLE: No.

38:53.360 --> 38:57.251
I explained them that me and Gaynor were
old war buddies. He tried to rope me in...

38:57.400 --> 38:59.607
[SIGHS]

38:59.760 --> 39:02.809
When I refused, he kidnapped Carly,
everything else happened under duress.

39:02.960 --> 39:04.007
[OLIVER SIGHS]

39:09.520 --> 39:11.648
I screwed up, Oliver.

39:13.680 --> 39:17.048
Obviously Gaynor wasn't
who I thought he was.

39:18.360 --> 39:20.408
I was wrong.

39:20.560 --> 39:25.361
Yeah, but you were right too.

39:28.320 --> 39:32.405
When you told me that I trusted the list
more than I trusted you.

39:33.440 --> 39:37.365
Diggle, the truth is,
after what happened to me on the island...

39:40.800 --> 39:45.886
...it's difficult for me to trust anything.

39:48.360 --> 39:49.521
But you do.

39:51.960 --> 39:55.009
And that reminded me
why I chose you as my partner.

39:56.560 --> 39:59.404
It's because you see the best in people.

40:34.280 --> 40:35.520
I learned something too.

40:37.600 --> 40:41.685
Until you tell me, I don't ever wanna know
what other names are in this book.

40:51.880 --> 40:53.928
OLIVER:
She promised she's not cheating on Walter.

40:54.080 --> 40:56.651
THEA: Like I would trust
anything that woman says.

40:56.800 --> 40:58.768
OFFICER:
Miss Queen? Thea Queen?

40:58.920 --> 41:01.571
- There a problem?
- We received a call from your doctor.

41:01.720 --> 41:05.770
In the event of a vehicular accident,
they report the results of the tox-screen.

41:05.920 --> 41:09.686
Ms. Queen tested positive
for a narcotic called Vertigo.

41:09.840 --> 41:10.887
[SIGHS]

41:11.040 --> 41:12.280
The drug they're using in the Glades?

41:12.440 --> 41:16.411
OFFICER: Thea Queen, you are under arrest
for driving under the influence of narcotics.

41:24.720 --> 41:28.122
Do you know why my men
wear balaclavas, Mr. Queen?

41:30.000 --> 41:32.970
Because it masks everything
but the eyes.

41:33.120 --> 41:37.170
And in a man's eyes,
one can always find the truth.

41:38.400 --> 41:41.802
You risked everything
to save your friend.

41:41.960 --> 41:44.406
Someone I warned you about...

41:44.600 --> 41:47.046
...and yet you trusted him.

41:47.200 --> 41:50.124
But that trust was misplaced.

42:30.680 --> 42:32.682
[English - US - SDH]
